Just like the three musketeers.

160
00:21:57,950 --> 00:22:00,384
也许有一天我能成为你的达达尼昂。
And maybe some day I can be your Dartagnan.

161
00:22:02,646 --> 00:22:06,917
- 玛丽在哪里? - 在里面。她会很高兴你回家的。到来。
- Where's Mary? - Inside. She'll be real happy you're home. Come along.

162
00:22:09,013 --> 00:22:10,188
Juanito!
Juanito!

163
00:22:12,703 --> 00:22:15,299
欢迎回家, 奇科。我很高兴见到你。
Welcome home, chico. I'm so happy to see you.

164
00:22:18,721 --> 00:22:21,674
玛丽为你准备了家里最好的房间。
Mary had the best room in the house prepared for you.

165
00:22:25,122 --> 00:22:27,446
- 欢迎回来，迪克 - 谢谢你，弗兰克。
- Welcome back, Dick. - Thank you, Frank.

166
00:22:27,696 --> 00:22:29,226
上来喝一杯吧。
Come on up and have a drink.

167
00:23:13,239 --> 00:23:15,838
迪克! 欢迎回家。
Dick! Welcome home.

168
00:23:16,824 --> 00:23:19,256
你穿制服真帅。
You look divine in your uniform.

169
00:23:19,921 --> 00:23:21,235
也许是这样。
That may be so.

170
00:23:21,971 --> 00:23:25,376
但我想他一定很想脱下来洗个热水澡。
But I imagine he's dying to get it off and take a hot bath.

171
00:23:25,519 --> 00:23:27,013
- 对吗? - 你说对了，爸爸。
- Isn't that right? - You said it, dad.

172
00:23:27,329 --> 00:23:28,789
空气是静止的。
The air's to still.

173
00:23:29,244 --> 00:23:30,737
龙卷风天气。
Tornado weather.

174
00:23:30,947 --> 00:23:33,274
不幸的是，情况会变得更糟。
It'll get worse, unfortunately.

175
00:23:33,523 --> 00:23:36,264
龙卷风来之前，都是这样。
That's the way it always is, before a tornado.

176
00:23:36,864 --> 00:23:41,204
还记得两年前的那个吗? 老人们说今晚会更糟。
Remember the one two yeras ago? Well, the old folks say that tonight will be even worse.

177
00:23:42,359 --> 00:23:45,456
你还在等什么? 你是来喝一杯的，对吧?
What are you waiting for? You came up for a drink, didn't you?

178
00:23:45,700 --> 00:23:47,716
- 继续，冲锋。- 我们会的，先生
- Go on, charge. - We will, sir.

179
00:23:48,483 --> 00:23:51,888
- 你有什么，儿子? - 现在没有，谢谢爸爸。我洗澡后。
- What do you have, son? - Nothing just now, thanks dad. After my bath.

180
00:23:52,520 --> 00:23:54,596
阿库姆巴少校，我跟你一起上去。
Major Acombar, I'll go up with you.

181
00:24:02,712 --> 00:24:03,779
哦, 爸爸。
Oh, dad.

182
00:24:04,104 --> 00:24:08,410
我差点忘了。在十字路口下车的陌生人
I almost forgot. A stranger that got off at the crossing...

183
00:24:08,698 --> 00:24:11,854
他说日落的时候会来这里。
Said he'd be paying a visit here at sundown.

184
00:24:12,559 --> 00:24:15,477
- 我想他是你的朋友 - 继续
- I think he's a friend of yours - Go on.

185
00:24:17,012 --> 00:24:18,994
- 他叫... - 给您，先生。
- His name is... - Here you are, sir.

186
00:24:21,952 --> 00:24:23,305
哦，是的，加里·汉密尔顿。
Oh yes, Gary Hamilton.

187
00:24:44,290 --> 00:24:47,101
- 那是什么? - 猛禽。
- What is that? - Bird of prey.

188
00:24:48,707 --> 00:24:50,261
龙卷风来了。
Por causa do tornado.

189
00:24:51,666 --> 00:24:54,761
动物察觉到麻烦，就会避开它。
Animals sense trouble, and avoid it.

190
00:24:58,972 --> 00:25:02,410
他把这个留在了舞台上。你能把它还给他吗?
He left this on the stage. Will you give it back to him?

191
00:25:04,571 --> 00:25:07,454
- 你来吗? - 当然, 迪克。是的。
- Are you coming? - Certainly, Dick. Yes.

192
00:25:09,618 --> 00:25:10,758
我们走吧。
Let's go.

193
00:25:18,560 --> 00:25:20,363
这是他的好吧，我记得很清楚。
It's his alright, I remember it well.

194
00:25:21,445 --> 00:25:24,400
我们把它放在马车上，作为对他不利的证据。
We put it on the stagecoach, as evidence against him.

195
00:25:24,647 --> 00:25:25,856
闭嘴!
Shut up!

196
00:25:28,753 --> 00:25:30,864
我不希望家里有人提起这件事。
I don't want this story mentioned in the house.

197
00:25:32,649 --> 00:25:35,711
如果他真要来，我们就等他。
If he really is coming, we'll wait for him.

198
00:25:36,547 --> 00:25:39,216
我们要确保他不能活着进来。
And we'll make sure he doesn't get in here alive.

199
00:25:40,131 --> 00:25:42,239
这也符合你的利益。
It's in your interest as well.

200
00:25:42,703 --> 00:25:45,409
记住:我的儿子绝对不能知道这件事。
And remember: My son mustn't know anything about this.

201
00:25:48,480 --> 00:25:51,185
他不会知道的，你放心吧，先生。
And he won't know, you can count on that, sir.

202
00:25:52,447 --> 00:25:54,985
把人叫来，到城外等我。
Get the men together and meet me outside of town.

203
00:26:00,415 --> 00:26:02,950
他被判终身监禁。你觉得他逃跑了吗?
He is in for life. Do you think he escaped?

204
00:26:03,091 --> 00:26:05,274
根本不可能知道。
There won't be any way of knowing.

205
00:26:06,850 --> 00:26:09,388
- 在他死后。- 万一发生什么事呢?
- After he's dead. - And if anything should happen?

206
00:26:10,539 --> 00:26:12,163
我要他死。
I want him dead.

207
00:26:13,878 --> 00:26:15,468
米格尔，你听到了吗?
Did you hear that, Miguel?

208
00:26:16,522 --> 00:26:19,892
阻止他。一劳永逸。
Stop him. Once and for all.

209
00:26:35,241 --> 00:26:36,795
出去。
Get out.

210
00:27:14,451 --> 00:27:16,703
鬼回来了。和他会...
A ghost returning. And he'll have...

211
00:27:18,175 --> 00:27:20,568
他心里只有一个愿望。
He'll have only one desire in his heart.

212
00:27:21,338 --> 00:27:24,043
只有一个干渴。报复。
Only one thirst. Revenge.

213
00:27:25,409 --> 00:27:26,869
你担心吗?
Are you worried?

214
00:27:27,219 --> 00:27:31,288
没有，但你儿子肯定怀疑我。
No, but your son must have suspected that I was.

215
00:27:32,367 --> 00:27:34,386
他问我是否认识加里·汉密尔顿。
He asked me if I knew Gary Hamilton.

216
00:27:35,639 --> 00:27:37,334
你怎么说?
And what did you say?

217
00:27:38,632 --> 00:27:42,972
我告诉他我不认识他。我从没听过这个名字。
I told him that I didn't know him. That I'd never heard the name before.

218
00:27:45,379 --> 00:27:47,847
但是，也许这就是事实。
But then, maybe that's the truth.

219
00:27:48,824 --> 00:27:51,077
我真的没有时间。
I really didn't get the time.

220
00:27:51,644 --> 00:27:53,517
去了解他
To get to know him.

221
00:27:55,818 --> 00:27:58,214
我只有时间
I only had the time

222
00:27:58,670 --> 00:28:00,130
背叛他。
to betray him.

223
00:28:02,009 --> 00:28:04,121
别说了，你又不认识他。
Let's keep it that way, you didn't know him.

224
00:28:04,862 --> 00:28:05,931
明白了吗?
Get it?

225
00:28:06,498 --> 00:28:08,087
一定不能让迪克知道。
Dick must never know.

226
00:28:08,761 --> 00:28:12,829
总之，汉米尔顿不可能活着进来。
Anyway, Hamilton will never get in here alive.

227
00:29:36,714 --> 00:29:39,217
不管谁来，都会受到热烈欢迎。
Whoever's coming's gonna get a rowdy welcome.

228
00:29:40,365 --> 00:29:41,990
你说呢，法官?
What do you say, judge?

229
00:29:54,946 --> 00:29:56,048
安妮!
Annie!

230
00:29:56,858 --> 00:29:58,353
嗨, 叔叔Johnathan。
Hi, uncle Johnathan.

231
00:30:02,633 --> 00:30:04,745
今晚真的要刮风了吗?
Is it true the wind's coming tonight?

232
00:30:05,937 --> 00:30:09,521
你拿命打赌。你最好待在室内。不许往窗外偷看。
You bet your life. And you better stay indoors. No peeking out the windows.

233
00:30:09,731 --> 00:30:12,162
稍后会有很多危险的爆炸。
There's gonna be lots of dangerous later blowing.

234
00:30:13,767 --> 00:30:15,261
它们在今晚的微风中飘荡。
They're blowing in the breeze tonight.

235
00:30:23,925 --> 00:30:25,136
安妮, 没有。
Annie, no.

236
00:30:25,421 --> 00:30:27,081
不，小家伙，不不不，等等。
Oh no, little one, no no no, wait.

237
00:30:27,509 --> 00:30:31,055
如果你把这些拿走，乔纳森叔叔什么也看不见。
Uncle Johnathan can't se a damned thing if you take these away.

238
00:30:34,189 --> 00:30:36,516
- 时间到了。风快来了 - 快走。
- The hour's now. The wind's almost here - Go on.

239
00:30:36,800 --> 00:30:38,745
确保他们尽快上床睡觉。
And you make sure they go to bed soon.

240
00:30:39,756 --> 00:30:44,584
你最好也待在屋里。如果阿库姆巴试图把风吓跑，我不会感到惊讶。
You better stay inside too. I wouldn't be surprised if Acombar tries to scare that wind away.

241
00:32:32,342 --> 00:32:33,730
他到底去哪儿了?
Where the hell did he go?

242
00:32:55,097 --> 00:32:57,172
有什么事吗? 你疯了吗?
What's the matter? You crazy or something?

243
00:33:00,140 --> 00:33:02,607
好吧，跟我来，跟紧点。
Alright, follow me, and keep close.

244
00:33:14,266 --> 00:33:18,300
在我们自相残杀之前赶紧回城里吧。我们。
Let's get back to town before we end up shooting amongst ourselves. Vamos.

245
00:33:36,534 --> 00:33:37,637
吉姆。
Jim.

246
00:33:41,681 --> 00:33:44,493
让我们分成小组。你和你的人去牧场前面。
Let's split up into groups. You go with your men to the front of the ranch.

247
00:33:44,953 --> 00:33:47,136
如果我们不先在这里找到他，他肯定会去那里。
If we don't find him here first, then he will go there for sure.

248
00:33:47,214 --> 00:33:48,459
对, 我们走吧。
Right, let's go.

249
00:33:58,731 --> 00:34:02,205
- Acombar真的在悬赏吗? - 对，大的。
- Is it true Acombar is offering a reward? - Si, a big one.

250
00:34:02,766 --> 00:34:04,603
得先抓住他。
Gotta catch him first.

251
00:34:15,188 --> 00:34:18,487
- 你在找谁? - 少管闲事，老头。
- Who are you looking for? - Mind your own business, old man.

252
00:34:18,807 --> 00:34:20,357
回你的房子去。
Go back into your house.

253
00:34:21,170 --> 00:34:22,416
留在原地。
Stay put too.

254
00:35:03,789 --> 00:35:05,105
该死的风。
Damn wind.

255
00:35:14,925 --> 00:35:16,028
我们。
Vamos.

256
00:35:18,545 --> 00:35:22,053
哪儿也找不到他。我们在原地打转。
He is nowhere to be found. We're running around in circles.

257
00:35:22,509 --> 00:35:26,020
如果我们继续这样下去，我们肯定会失去那1万美元的奖金。
If we keep this up, we'll lose that 10,000 dollar award for sure.

258
00:39:44,038 --> 00:39:45,354
为什么今晚?
Why tonight?

259
00:39:46,404 --> 00:39:48,313
他今晚为什么要按铃?
What's he ringing the bell tonight for?

260
00:39:48,492 --> 00:39:53,641
不可能是部长。我看见他把门铃系在前门。
Can't be the minister. I saw him tie up that bell by the front door.

261
00:39:54,303 --> 00:39:56,449
一定是别人把它解开的。
Somebody else must have untied it.

262
00:40:50,630 --> 00:40:52,090
它会给我们带来坏运气。
It'll bring us bad luck.

263
00:41:08,686 --> 00:41:09,790
吉姆。
Jim.

264
00:41:49,010 --> 00:41:50,433
骗子, 骗子, 骗子!
Liar, liar, liar!

265
00:42:00,907 --> 00:42:02,640
我准备好喝一杯了。
I'm ready for that drink now.

266
00:42:03,900 --> 00:42:07,542
你长得真像，我都快认不出你了。
Well you do look like that, I hardly recognized you.

267
00:42:09,398 --> 00:42:12,423
- 今晚怎么了? - 一定是风。
- What's going on tonight? - Must be the wind.

268
00:42:13,156 --> 00:42:15,375
- 贝尔被解开了。- 那枪声呢?
- Bell got untied. - What about the gunfire?

269
00:42:16,704 --> 00:42:20,559
可能只是喝醉了，想把龙卷风吓跑。
Probably just some drunk, trying to scare the tornado away.

270
00:42:22,514 --> 00:42:24,696
让我们为你的归来干杯。
Let's drink to your return.

271
00:42:26,933 --> 00:42:28,878
你想尝尝这个吗?
And would you like to try some of this?

272
00:42:29,090 --> 00:42:30,120
不。
No.

273
00:44:21,259 --> 00:44:22,268
吉姆!
Jim!

274
00:44:25,328 --> 00:44:26,468
吉姆!
Jim!

275
00:44:31,104 --> 00:44:32,457
没有, 吉姆。
No, Jim.

276
00:44:36,741 --> 00:44:37,774
吉姆!
Jim!

277
00:45:50,743 --> 00:45:52,548
谁按的铃?
Who rang the bell?

278
00:45:56,729 --> 00:45:59,122
一定是汉密尔顿。那不是鬼。
It must have been Hamilton. It was not a ghost.

279
00:46:00,345 --> 00:46:01,839
我将警告Acombar。
I'll warn Acombar.

280
00:46:05,982 --> 00:46:07,605
我就呆在这里。
I'll stick around here.

281
00:46:33,155 --> 00:46:34,816
我杀了他，父亲。
I killed him, father.

282
00:46:36,460 --> 00:46:39,554
父亲，我为什么叫你父亲?
Father, what am I doing calling you father?

283
00:46:40,981 --> 00:46:43,652
我为什么要跟一个相信
And what am I doing talking to a man that believes in the

284
00:46:44,532 --> 00:46:46,299
宽容的上帝吗?
forgiving God?

285
00:46:47,836 --> 00:46:53,365
我想让你知道加里·汉密尔顿已经被判终身监禁了。
I want you to know that Gary Hamilton has got a life sentence engraved in his skin.

286
00:46:55,803 --> 00:46:59,514
一天又一天，他们说服我，我的位置在里面。
Day after day they convinced me that my place was inside.

287
00:47:00,883 --> 00:47:02,994
外面的生活对我来说已经没有意义了。
Life outside has no more meaning for me.

288
00:47:04,223 --> 00:47:05,847
现在只有复仇了。
Now it's only revenge.

289
00:47:09,895 --> 00:47:12,850
这样就能解决其中一个了。等我把剩下的都弄好了...
That takes care of one of them. Now when I'm finished with the rest of them...

290
00:47:13,514 --> 00:47:14,758
圣玛丽
Santa Marias,

291
00:47:18,661 --> 00:47:20,215
Acombar自己。
Acombar himself.

292
00:47:23,114 --> 00:47:26,033
我已经花了十年的时间来考虑我的复仇计划。
I've had ten long years to think out my revenge.

293
00:47:27,986 --> 00:47:31,495
如果无辜的人被判入狱，那我就有权杀人。
If innocents is repaid with prison, then I've earned the right to kill.

294
00:47:37,416 --> 00:47:38,943
你听见了吗，父亲?
Do you hear me, father?

295
00:47:41,032 --> 00:47:43,286
即使上帝会因此惩罚我。
Even if God chooses to punish me for it.

296
00:47:51,158 --> 00:47:54,871
是的，他不知怎么进来了，然后，
Yes, he got in somehow, and then,

297
00:47:55,959 --> 00:47:57,382
他杀害了吉姆。
he killed Jim.

298
00:47:57,699 --> 00:48:00,237
别告诉我你被一个人骗了。
Don't tell me you allowed yourself to be tricked by one man.

299
00:48:00,690 --> 00:48:04,201
你有30多个人。你一定要找到他。
You've got more than 30 men. You've got to find him.

300
00:48:06,569 --> 00:48:08,337
谁在敲教堂的钟?
Who was ringing the church bell?

301
00:48:09,285 --> 00:48:10,600
- 也许他。- 爸爸。
- Maybe him. - Dad.

302
00:48:11,023 --> 00:48:13,171
你不太忙吗? 晚饭准备好了。
You're not too busy? Dinner's ready.

303
00:48:13,911 --> 00:48:15,300
我马上就来。
I'll be right there.

304
00:48:58,340 --> 00:48:59,371
传播出去。
Spread out.

305
00:50:33,008 --> 00:50:35,749
爸爸，听起来今晚有很多酒鬼在外面。
Dad, it sound like there are many drunks out tonight.

306
00:50:57,780 --> 00:50:59,095
你还想再来点吗?
Would you like some more?

307
00:51:34,104 --> 00:51:35,693
在这里, 乔。快。
Down here, Joe. Quick.

308
00:52:31,300 --> 00:52:32,439
加里!
Gary!

309
00:52:33,179 --> 00:52:34,390
妈的，我就知道。
Son of a gun, I knew it.

310
00:52:37,148 --> 00:52:40,514
我知道那是你，知道你会来这里。
I knew darn well it was you, and that you'd come here.

311
00:52:40,763 --> 00:52:42,875
所以我才替你把架子从井里拿下来。
That's why I took the rack off the well for you.

312
00:52:43,234 --> 00:52:47,682
你骑着马消失的时候我以为你会躲到地下
You see when you disappeared on that horse I figured you'd go under ground to the

313
00:52:48,000 --> 00:52:49,769
古老的印度墓园。
old indian cemetary.

314
00:52:54,820 --> 00:52:57,359
当我还是个孩子的时候，我们在那待过很长时间。
We spent a lot of time down there when I was a kid.

315
00:52:58,194 --> 00:53:01,599
你知道自从你入狱后一切都变了。
You know things ain't never been the same since you got put away.

316
00:53:03,203 --> 00:53:04,757
关于唯一一个...
About the only person that...

317
00:53:08,075 --> 00:53:11,374
让她昂首阔步的是罗斯。其余的人都害怕阿库姆巴。
That has kept her head high has been Rosy. The rest are scared of Acombar.

318
00:53:12,563 --> 00:53:16,418
她为此付出了沉重的代价。开枪打死了她的丈夫约翰尼。
She's had to pay dearly. The shot and killed Johnny, her husband.

319
00:53:16,844 --> 00:53:19,345
他们称之为“意外”。
And the called it "an accident".

320
00:53:21,817 --> 00:53:23,726
- 法官呢? - 法官?
- And the judge? - The judge?

321
00:53:25,541 --> 00:53:28,280
他们能买到的第一批。
One of the first they could buy.

322
00:53:28,881 --> 00:53:30,719
你的腿怎么了?
What happened to your leg?

323
00:53:32,116 --> 00:53:34,787
这是一个旧金山的圣马尔韆的礼物。
That was a present from Francisco Santa Mar韆.

324
00:53:36,084 --> 00:53:38,098
- 事故? - 还有什么?
